Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 813 "The \NShadow Approaching Amuro"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.02,0:00:04.20,Poirot,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Poirot
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.75,0:00:17.24,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.07,0:00:19.54,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Here are your ham sandwiches.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.53,0:00:43.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.24,0:00:46.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You've been watching that \Ncustomer this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.20,0:00:47.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.94,0:00:51.14,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:52.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.70,0:00:55.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.11,0:00:58.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,while reading about the races in \Nthe paper and eating breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.16,0:01:00.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I am a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.17,0:01:05.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's not dressed like a salary man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.39,0:01:09.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But he's at a café before work hours start.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.83,0:01:11.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what's bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.94,0:01:16.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Some people are like that. We're like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:22.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But he ordered sandwiches \Ninstead of the breakfast set
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.71,0:01:27.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,most customers order at this hour \Nwithout even looking at the menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.06,0:01:30.30,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean he's a regular?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.30,0:01:34.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But he's not speaking to \NAmuro-san or Azusa-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.83,0:01:38.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and he's been watching the \Ncounter this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.43,0:01:41.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.71,0:01:44.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He's interested in Azusa-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.54,0:01:47.55,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, of course. You really \Nare a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.55,0:01:49.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I could handle that mystery \Nbefore I even have breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.59,0:01:52.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, while I eat breakfast!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.05,0:01:57.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, he's been watching not Azusa-san, \Nbut Amuro-san this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.38,0:02:00.67,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.09,0:02:04.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With the same feelings we've \Nalways held still in our hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.78,0:02:07.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we fly powerfully into our twentieth year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.05,0:02:11.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An unexpected figure closes in on Amuro \NToru, who works at the Poirot Café.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.20,0:02:14.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.72,0:02:17.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:04:04.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(404,1)}The Shadow Approaching Amuro
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.71,0:04:01.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Shadow Approaching Amuro!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.83,0:04:08.22,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? We're playing games at \Nthe professor's house again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.22,0:04:10.53,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's all we've been doing lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:12.40,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to do, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.40,0:04:16.37,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You were assigned homework \Ntoday. You should do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.37,0:04:20.69,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then like Haibara-san says, \Nwe should do our homework first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.63,0:04:22.57,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}No way. Let's play games.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:24.95,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.30,0:04:28.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was at Poirot this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.72,0:04:32.83,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He probably lives or works nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.06,0:04:35.27,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so interested in that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.27,0:04:37.58,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's interested in everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.96,0:04:43.16,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But there's always a case \Nwhen Conan-kun is interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.16,0:04:44.83,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.83,0:04:45.97,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He's coming out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.79,0:04:57.98,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,If you're so curious, let's follow him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.29,0:04:59.90,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:03.11,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds more interesting than \Nplaying games at the professor's!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.11,0:05:06.07,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like something the \NDetective Boys would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:07.86,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.86,0:05:08.84,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.78,0:05:12.32,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let him notice you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.98,0:05:14.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:16.86,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun and Ai-chan, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.86,0:05:18.29,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.29,0:05:22.14,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't follow him for too long. \NYou should go home and do your homework!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.90,0:05:25.40,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,This is your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.40,0:05:28.52,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure those kids get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.60,0:05:35.52,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.52,0:05:36.58,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,You're alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.58,0:05:38.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.70,0:05:41.53,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,The man who just left?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.03,0:05:42.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.83,0:05:47.70,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know his name, but he \Nhas been coming a lot lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.10,0:05:49.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What does he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.66,0:05:51.45,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:27.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone. He disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.15,0:06:30.82,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He must have gone into a store.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:34.08,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's split up and \Ncheck all the stores!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:35.66,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.92,0:06:39.46,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,He was watching me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.74,0:06:42.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it looked that way to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.47,0:06:45.21,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it did. I saw the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.61,0:06:48.05,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,And he even followed me the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.26,0:06:49.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He followed you? When?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.45,0:06:56.06,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Three days ago, I think, when I \Nwent shopping at the supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.06,0:06:57.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.38,0:06:59.60,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,And what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.60,0:07:01.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're just ignoring him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:03.73,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not as though \Nhe's done anything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.60,0:07:06.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A member of the organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.23,0:07:09.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he could be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.73,0:07:11.17,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.17,0:07:16.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't know all the members \Nof the Black Organization, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.20,0:07:17.50,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.50,0:07:20.37,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't get that feeling from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.41,0:07:27.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible he's a public \Nsecurity officer like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.03,0:07:32.86,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I see you love investigating as much as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.18,0:07:42.69,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.69,0:07:44.75,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.58,0:07:47.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,We checked all the shops, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.18,0:07:50.82,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but he wasn't at any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.34,0:07:54.57,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He must've disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.78,0:07:59.83,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.15,0:08:02.49,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared in the shopping area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.49,0:08:03.53,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.53,0:08:06.16,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He must be hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.96,0:08:09.45,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Amuro-no-niichan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.04,0:08:16.97,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.48,0:08:20.38,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I just remembered I have \Nsomething to do. I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.38,0:08:22.04,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Ai-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:25.81,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is your fault, Genta-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.81,0:08:27.37,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.08,0:08:29.65,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.82,0:08:44.31,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.31,0:08:48.26,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. Why is he following Amuro-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.26,0:08:50.86,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,This is getting more and more suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.61,0:09:13.24,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.56,0:09:15.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a dead end up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.90,0:09:23.92,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have business with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:30.06,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. I have business this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.06,0:09:32.42,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,This is a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.96,0:09:36.45,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You've been coming to Poirot a lot lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.00,0:09:40.36,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you following me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.34,0:10:07.04,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:09.02,DCItalic,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro-san, it's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.30,0:10:11.07,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.43,0:10:13.11,DCItalic,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Go buy some ice cream!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.14,0:10:15.79,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Ice cream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:17.99,DCItalic,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,We accepted an order for an ice cream soda,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.99,0:10:20.30,DCItalic,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,even though the manager\Nforgot to order some!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.71,0:10:22.38,DCItalic,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Go buy some as soon as you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.56,0:10:28.18,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.57,0:10:48.07,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.07,0:10:50.30,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same shopping area as yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.81,0:10:52.76,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's search all the stores again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.76,0:10:53.46,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.81,0:11:07.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.06,0:11:09.46,DCItalic,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.41,0:11:11.85,DCItalic,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Here are your ham sandwiches.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.61,0:11:19.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He ordered sandwiches instead of the breakfast\Nset most customers order at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.29,0:11:40.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was at Poirot this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.64,0:11:44.99,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He probably lives or works nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.21,0:11:47.81,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,He was watching me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.81,0:11:50.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it looked that way to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:53.56,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it did. I saw the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.85,0:11:56.40,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,And he even followed me the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:58.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He followed you? When?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.72,0:12:04.16,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Three days ago, I think, when I \Nwent shopping at the supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.68,0:12:07.04,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.15,0:12:11.29,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. He wasn't in any of the stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.29,0:12:12.74,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't find him, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.74,0:12:14.72,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,How about this store?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.29,0:12:17.92,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He's not in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:20.44,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.44,0:12:21.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:22.69,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:24.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He'll appear soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.68,0:12:26.68,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.69,0:12:31.34,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.34,0:12:34.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's late. Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:36.19,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.60,0:12:40.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro-san knew he was following him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:41.99,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.39,0:12:45.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.27,0:12:47.88,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.24,0:13:03.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.56,0:13:09.81,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:14.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.45,0:13:16.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...a baker, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.20,0:13:17.93,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:20.02,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,A baker?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.11,0:13:26.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, he had sandwiches here \Nin the morning and evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.68,0:13:29.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sandwiches made by Amuro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.27,0:13:33.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He always keeps his fingernails clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:34.88,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.56,0:13:40.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And he has a distinctive \Nmark on his forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.87,0:13:44.48,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,What is that mark on his head?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:45.42,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Is it from a hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.75,0:13:47.93,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It's from elastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.15,0:13:51.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. A hat with an elastic band.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.97,0:13:58.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the type of hat worn by \Ncooks who work with starchy foods,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.01,0:14:02.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,like bread or noodles, in the kitchen \Ninstead of interacting with customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.46,0:14:04.94,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, \Nthere's one in the shopping area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.18,0:14:08.52,DCItalic,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. He wasn't in any of the stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.52,0:14:09.80,DCItalic,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't find him, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.80,0:14:11.65,DCItalic,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,How about this store?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.17,0:14:14.95,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,There was a bakery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.23,0:14:19.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A baker who doesn't interact \Nwith customers makes bread
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:24.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,early in the morning and makes more \Nas necessary in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.95,0:14:29.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's not dressed like a salary man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.19,0:14:34.39,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But he's at a café before work hours start.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.71,0:14:36.51,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what's bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.82,0:14:39.77,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Some people are like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:45.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, his job allows him a lot \Nof free time in mornings and evenings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:49.32,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. He didn't disappear, \Nhe went inside the bakery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.49,0:14:52.12,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,So he was an employee, not a customer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.38,0:14:54.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, if you wait outside \Nthe bakery long enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.26,0:14:57.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he'll change in the back \Nand show himself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.29,0:15:00.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,At least, that's what I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:03.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but he didn't appear no matter \Nhow long we waited before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.82,0:15:06.49,DCItalic,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.49,0:15:10.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's late. Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.51,0:15:11.26,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.74,0:15:15.18,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro-san knew he was following him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:17.18,DCItalic,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.60,0:15:23.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When Amuro-san noticed him, I thought \Nhe might make a desperate final play.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.90,0:15:26.94,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,A final play?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.43,0:15:29.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to ask him directly, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.73,0:15:35.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,About how Amuro-san makes his sandwiches.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.58,0:15:36.55,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.55,0:15:37.83,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.10,0:15:42.52,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that lately the sandwiches \Nhere have been delicious and cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.52,0:15:44.14,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,When I came to try them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.86,0:15:48.92,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was shocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.12,0:15:54.26,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,...by how delicious they were!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.61,0:15:56.79,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,The ham sandwiches were especially fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.20,0:16:03.89,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to make sandwiches \Nthis delicious myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.09,0:16:09.38,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,But no matter how much I watched \Nyou, I couldn't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.01,0:16:25.31,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,So I followed you and examined the bread,\Nham, lettuce, and mayonnaise you bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.77,0:16:31.51,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,But you weren't buying anything special.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.15,0:16:34.48,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even when I tried to make them \Nwith the same ingredients,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.48,0:16:36.63,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't achieve the same flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.28,0:16:40.29,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,How do you make such delicious sandwiches?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.80,0:16:44.61,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's all I thought about every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:47.37,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd go crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.51,0:16:53.28,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,How?! How do you make such \Ndelicious ham sandwiches?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.31,0:17:03.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, that's Amuro-san's trade secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.26,0:17:06.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:10.30,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.80,0:17:13.34,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.75,0:17:15.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.05,0:17:22.22,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Cheap ham is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.91,0:17:26.02,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But choose the leanest pieces possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.53,0:17:28.75,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Then coat them in olive oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.70,0:17:33.78,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. The rich flavor of \Nthe ham comes from olive oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.10,0:17:36.78,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:40.03,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I use ordinary mayonnaise as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.54,0:17:45.29,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Miso?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.54,0:17:48.79,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why there was \Nmiso in the refrigerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.13,0:17:51.71,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Just use a pinch of miso.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.48,0:17:57.33,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Putting miso in mayonnaise tastes good?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.33,0:18:00.68,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Olive oil and miso are \Nan excellent combination.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.04,0:18:06.18,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. The sauce complements \Nthe olive oil covered ham.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.65,0:18:11.82,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,This is ordinary hot water, \Nand this is ordinary lettuce.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:16.19,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.50,0:18:19.13,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Have you noticed that if the \Ninside of the sandwich is cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.13,0:18:23.93,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,you only feel the coldness \Ninstead of tasting the flavors?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.44,0:18:25.64,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.64,0:18:26.20,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.44,0:18:30.17,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't thinking about \Nthat while I was eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.17,0:18:32.56,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Now you don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.32,0:18:35.75,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But it'll make the lettuce soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.75,0:18:37.42,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:41.58,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.58,0:18:44.68,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Using water the temperature \Nof bath water is the secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.36,0:18:49.12,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, the lettuce will \Nkeep its crispness for longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.12,0:18:51.73,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,even if kept between bread if you do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.98,0:18:55.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro-san, who on earth are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.33,0:18:58.54,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Now for the bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.54,0:19:00.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,This type of bread is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.71,0:19:01.61,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.93,0:19:03.57,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you were using?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.57,0:19:06.28,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It cuts the price in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.28,0:19:08.60,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.00,0:19:10.21,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the flavor...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.63,0:19:14.36,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, slightly stale bread is better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.36,0:19:15.84,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.14,0:19:17.45,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,This is my secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.87,0:19:19.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A steamer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.39,0:19:25.33,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Try touching the bread inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.65,0:19:30.73,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Wow. It's so soft!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.09,0:19:34.32,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I steam them slightly \Nbefore making sandwiches.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.32,0:19:38.22,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,The bread will absorb all \Nthe moisture it lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.22,0:19:42.52,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's why they were warm \Neven though you didn't toast them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:45.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,And it keeps the cost down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.97,0:19:50.26,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro-san was taking his \Ncafé job seriously, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:54.87,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's the miso mayonnaise sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.24,0:20:01.58,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But this softness doesn't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.08,0:20:06.95,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It's good for eating in the store, \Nbut not great for takeout.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.53,0:20:09.02,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a baker.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.53,0:20:12.00,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can do something about the bread, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.49,0:20:16.76,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,So please let me sell your \Nsandwiches at my store!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.19,0:20:18.15,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.53,0:20:21.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, you're asking for too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.74,0:20:22.96,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.73,0:20:25.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.07,0:20:28.92,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You fell in love with my ham sandwiches.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.92,0:20:31.16,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the kind of man I want to sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.26,0:22:08.26,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,They're ready. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:10.52,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.28,0:22:12.06,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.06,0:22:13.79,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's so soft!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.79,0:22:15.52,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,This sauce is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.91,0:22:19.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. The bread is warm, \Nand it's not cold on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.08,0:22:22.26,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is it. This flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.59,0:22:26.55,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I think selling them in the store at Poirot
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.55,0:22:32.28,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,and selling them to take home \Nat your bakery is a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.71,0:22:34.33,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.33,0:22:39.70,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll develop a bread that stays soft for hours,\Nand do my best to faithfully recreate these.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.70,0:22:42.46,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I swear I won't sully Poirot's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.76,0:22:45.18,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.18,0:22:48.70,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, if you're going \Nto use the Poirot name,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.70,0:22:51.41,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,we should get permission \Nfrom the manager first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:54.47,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.03,0:22:56.73,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,This is Amuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.73,0:22:58.18,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Bourbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.29,0:23:02.40,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Vermouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.87,0:23:07.60,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you've been conducting \Na secret investigation recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.13,0:23:10.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,An investigation? Into what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.55,0:23:18.77,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be calling you if I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.57,0:23:20.71,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.34,0:23:23.80,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take it too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.14,0:23:26.71,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he has his eye on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.17,0:23:30.58,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,He has his eye on me? Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.82,0:23:33.09,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Gin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.00,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.40,0:23:47.41,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.41,0:23:49.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shono Kyona's blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.10,0:23:52.60,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, she mentioned something...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.60,0:23:56.65,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,...that suggested Kitami Saya's \Nsecrets were on her blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.65,0:23:57.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.00,0:23:59.80,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.80,0:24:01.50,DCMain,RECEPTION,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.76,0:24:04.91,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kyono-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.00,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Actress Blogger's Locked Room Case\N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.63,0:24:14.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The Actress \NBlogger's Locked Room Case, Part One!"
